chargeHist.descr: Cause Child 13-18 to View Sex. Activity

result.execSummary:
The defendant Zachary D Hetchler was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Cause Child 13-18 to View Sex. Activity, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.055(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: No contact, directly or indirectly, with co-defendants - Devin Copas and Morgan Pipkin, without the prior written consent of the agent (this includes face-to-face, third party, telephone, mail or electronic).    No contact with: Greg Ottinger, Rachel Hansen, Catherine and Brian Schneider, Edward Norris Jr, Jackie Bornsen, Richard Katlin and Harold Steel.  Except for incident contact, no contact with: anyone under the age of 18 without permission from the agent.    Not to possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substance not prescribed by authorized medical personnel.  Not to possess or consume any illegal drugs.  Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Not to associate with anyone using, possessing or distributing illegal drugs or involved in illegal drug activities.    Not to go on any premises where primary purpose is the sale of alcohol.

$1,734 represents restitution owed plus $173.40 restitution surcharge.  Joint and several.  To pay not less than $75 per month, when employed, towards restitution.  Provide completed Wage Assignment to the agent.
Pursuant to Amended Restitution Order (DOC-31) dated 04/04/2016, $1,233.03 represents restitution plus $173.40 restitution surcharge.  Co-defendant Morgan P. had $501 seized that was applied to the restitution owed in 14CM466.

Plus supervision fees.    If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.    $250 represents DNA surcharge.
Any assessment and counseling as required and follow through and complete all required treatment.
Write letter of apology to each victim, within 30 days - to be provided to the agent.    Submit a DNA sample.
